sections.heading: of private persons to bring action
sections.text: Any private person may on his own relation sue out writs of mandamus without application to the prosecuting attorney.SourceR.S.1867, Code § 2, p. 279;R.S.1913, § 8283;C.S.1922, § 9236;C.S.1929, § 20-2168;R.S.1943, § 25-2168.AnnotationsPrivate person may on his own
